{"lemma":"حَبِيب","slug":"حَبِيب","root":"ح.ب.ب","root_slug":"ح-ب-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-ب-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun_prop","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":7},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n6857"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%90%D9%8A%D8%A8"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"beloved"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"agreeable"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"beloved","examples":[{"text":"وَقَالَتِ ٱلْيَهُودُ وَٱلنَّصَارَى نَحْنُ أَبْنَاءُ ٱللّٰهِ وَأَحِبَّاؤُهُ قُلْ فَلِمَ يُعَذِّبُكُم بِذُنُوبِكُم بَلْ أَنْتُم بَشَرٌ مِمَّنْ خَلَقَ يَغْفِرُ لِمَن يَشَاءُ وَيُعَذِّبُ مَن يَشَاءُ وَلِلّٰهِ مُلْكُ ٱلسَّمَاوَاتِ وَٱلْأَرْضِ وَمَا بَيْنَهُمَا وَإِلَيْهِ ٱلْمَصِيرُ","english":"But the Jews and the Christians say, \"We are the children of Allah and His beloved.\" Say, \"Then why does He punish you for your sins?\" Rather, you are human beings from among those He has created. He forgives whom He wills, and He punishes whom He wills. And to Allah belongs the dominion of the heavens and the earth and whatever is between them, and to Him is the [final] destination."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"sweetheart"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"dear"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"darling","examples":[{"text":"يَا حَبِيبِي!","english":"oh my darling!"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"frequently used title of God, the Beloved, the Focus of one's heart and devotion"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From the root ح ب ب (ḥ b b). Compare Hebrew חָבִיב (ḥāḇīḇ), Classical Syriac ܚܒܝܒܐ (ḥabbīḇā)."},"ipa":["/ħa.biːb/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n6857","headword_ar":"حَبِيبٌ","root":"Hb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"A person"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"loved, beloved, affected, liked,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"approved;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * A, Msb, * K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHobuwbN","text_ar":"مَحْبُوبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHab~N","text_ar":"مُحَبٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) of which two the former is generally used for the latter, (S, K, TA,) in like manner as are used"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mazokuwmN","text_ar":"مَزْكُومٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHozuwnN","text_ar":"مَحْزُونٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"majonuwnN","text_ar":"مَجْنُونٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"makozuwzN","text_ar":"مَكْزُوزٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maqoruwrN","text_ar":"مَقْرُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", each of which has its proper verb of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuEila","text_ar":"فُعِلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hib~N","text_ar":"حِبٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HubaAbN","text_ar":"حُبَابٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hub~FpN","text_ar":"حُبًّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", which last is also applied to a female, and has for its pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HubabN","text_ar":"حُبَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) the fem. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HabiybN","text_ar":"حَبِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb, K;) and so is that of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHobuwbN","text_ar":"مَحْبُوبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) [and that of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHab~N","text_ar":"مُحَبٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":",] and that of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hib~N","text_ar":"حِبٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HabiybN","text_ar":"حَبِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHib~aA='u","text_ar":"اَحِبَّا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", instead of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HubabaA='u","text_ar":"حُبَبَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which would be the reg. pl. but for the repetition of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"b","text_ar":"ب"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HabiybapN","text_ar":"حَبِيبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HabaAy^ibu","text_ar":"حَبَايِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) the pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hib~N","text_ar":"حِبٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHobaAbN","text_ar":"اَحْبَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[a pl. of pauc.] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hib~aAnN","text_ar":"حِبَّانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hub~aAnN","text_ar":"حُبَّانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(MF) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HubuwbN","text_ar":"حُبُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HibabapN","text_ar":"حِبَبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hub~N","text_ar":"حُبٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", which last is rare ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaziyzN","text_ar":"عَزِيزٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":") [as a pl.], or is a quasi-pl. n. (K.) Though ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHab~N","text_ar":"مُحَبٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is uncommon it occurs in the following verse of 'Antarah:"},{"kind":"quote","text":"walaqado nazalot falaA taZun~Y gayorahu\n                      \n                     \n                        min~iY bimonozilapi AlmuHab~i Almukorami"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And thou hast taken (and imagine not otherwise), in respect of me,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. of my heart,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the place of the beloved, the honoured;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"become in the condition of the beloved,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (T, TA.) ―         -b2-  Also, (IAar, KL, TA,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hib~N","text_ar":"حِبٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, KL,) A person"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"loving; a lover; a friend;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(KL;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHib~N","text_ar":"مُحِبٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (IAar, K, TA:) [fem. of each with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":":] the pl. of the first (i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hbyb","text_ar":"حبيب"},{"kind":"text","text":") is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHobaAbN","text_ar":"اَحْبَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) [and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHib~aA='u","text_ar":"اَحِبَّا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHib~apN","text_ar":"اَحِبَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", mentioned by Golius as from the S, but not in my copies of the S: both, however, are correct: the former, the more common: the latter, a pl. of pauc.]. You say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AimoraA^apN","text_ar":"اِمْرَاَةٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lizawojihaA","text_ar":"لِزَوْجِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHib~apN","text_ar":"مُحِبَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHib~N","text_ar":"مُحِبٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A woman loving to her husband"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Fr, S, K. *) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abuw HabiybK","text_ar":"اَبُو حَبِيبٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The kid."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Har p. 227.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHabiybapu","text_ar":"الحَبِيبَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHab~N","text_ar":"مُحَبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","TA","MF","IAar","KL"]}]}}